        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 3:45PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near East Lemolo Campground to near Crater Lake
Lodge. Movement was north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
East Lemolo Campground, Crater Lake Lodge, Highway 138 Diamond Lake
Summit, Diamond Lake, Broken Arrow Campground, Digit Point Campground
At Miller Lake, and Thielsen View Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
